FIG. 8 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 400 of FIG. 7 to correct the wheel speed;


FIG. 9 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in steps 420 and 430 of FIG. 7 to determine front and rear wheel state variables;


FIG. 10 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 40 of FIG. 3 to determine the state of a vehicle;


FIG. 11 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 730 of FIG. 10 to determine instability of behavior of a vehicle body


FIG. 12 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 810 of FIG. 11 to calculate front and rear state variables for determining instability of behavior of a vehicle body;


FIG. 13 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 820 of FIG. 11 to determine the type of instability of behavior of a vehicle body;


FIG. 14 is an illustration which shows the types of instability of behavior of a vehicle body determined in terms of front and rear state variables;


FIG. 15 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 720 of FIG. 10 to determine stability of behavior of a vehicle body;


FIG. 16 is a flowchart of a sub-program executed in step 50 of FIG. 3 to determine a controlled variable for each wheel;


FIG. 17 is a graph which shows the relation between a state parameter and basic controlled variables;


